timing_extract...ck_arcs_as_lvf(25.10)  timing_extract...ck_arcs_as_lvf(25.10)

Name
       timing_extract_model_check_arcs_as_lvf

Syntax
       timing_extract_model_check_arcs_as_lvf {true | false}

       Default: true

       Enables  check  arcs  to  be modeled as LVF arcs. By default, the check
       arcs will be written as nSigma numbers.

       Innovus allows you to write mean+/-nSigma values for  constraint  arcs,
       while  writing  separate mean and sigma values for delay and transition
       data.    This    can    be    enabled     by     setting     timing_ex-
       tract_model_check_arcs_as_lvf  global  variable to false and timing_ex-
       tract_model_write_lvf to true.

       This  global  variable  will  not  have  any   impact   if   timing_ex-
       tract_model_write_lvf is set to false.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

